        "# NYC Subway Fare Hikes and Ridership Elasticity Timeline (1904 - 2026)\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook constructs a comprehensive, data-driven historical timeline of the New York City MTA Subway fare increases from its inception in 1904 through the milestone $3.00 fare hike in January 2026. By marrying historical nominal fare data with actual annual ridership figures and adjusting for inflation via the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) Consumer Price Index (CPI), this project quantifies the Price Elasticity of Demand ($E_d$) across over a century of transit policy. The notebook automatically scrapes live macroeconomic data from FRED to calibrate historical pricing to 2026 equivalent dollars, maps structural technological shifts (Tokens, MetroCards, OMNY, and Congestion Pricing), and provides an interactive visualization of the elasticity of urban transit."
