        "## Step 3: Compute Price Elasticity of Demand ($E_d$) Timeline\n",
        "\n",
        "Price Elasticity of Demand measures the responsiveness of quantity demanded (ridership) to a change in real price. We utilize the Midpoint (Arc) Elasticity formula to avoid directional bias between sequential historical tracking points:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$E_d = \\frac{(Q_2 - Q_1) / [(Q_1 + Q_2) / 2]}{(P_2 - P_1) / [(P_1 + P_2) / 2]}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "*Interpretation:*\n",
        "*   $-1 < E_d \\le 0$: Inelastic demand (commuters accept the hike with minimal dropoff).\n",
        "*   $E_d < -1$: Elastic demand (price hikes drive substantial ridership attrition)."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SEIMmnV4RMY8"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "elasticities = [np.nan] # First entry cannot have a prior delta calculation\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(1, len(df)):\n",
        "    q1 = df.loc[i-1, 'annual_riders_millions']\n",
        "    q2 = df.loc[i, 'annual_riders_millions']\n",
        "    p1 = df.loc[i-1, 'real_fare_2026_dollars']\n",
        "    p2 = df.loc[i, 'real_fare_2026_dollars']\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Calculate percentage changes using the midpoints\n",
        "    pct_change_q = (q2 - q1) / ((q1 + q2) / 2) if (q1 + q2) != 0 else 0\n",
        "    pct_change_p = (p2 - p1) / ((p1 + p2) / 2) if (p1 + p2) != 0 else 0\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Compute elasticity coefficient; protect against zero division\n",
        "    if pct_change_p == 0:\n",
        "        ed = 0.0\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        ed = pct_change_q / pct_change_p\n",
        "        \n",
        "    elasticities.append(round(ed, 3))\n",
        "\n",
        "df['price_elasticity_of_demand'] = elasticities\n",
        "# Display calculation outcomes table\n",
        "df[['year', 'nominal_fare', 'real_fare_2026_dollars', 'annual_riders_millions', 'price_elasticity_of_demand', 'event']]"
